cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.LG 

The paper discusses the use of memristor networks for analog approximate computation in the context of machine learning, specifically reservoir computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the dynamics and properties of memristors, which falls under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of memristors for analog computation, which falls under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). The paper also discusses the implications of device variability on the performance of memristor networks, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the computational performance of different memristor models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
